ollowing the formal events  cadets will be able to enjoy a picnic lunch with their families and friends  Box lunches will be provided to all cadets  as well as for those family members who purchased tickets on Matriculation Day from the Parents Council Those who did not buy tickets on Matriculation Day for box lunches may purchase food in New Market or bring their own picnic lunch  The events at New Market conclude with a parade through the town after lunch  Cadets must return to Post on the buses  but will be able to sign out to spend time that evening with their parents in Lexington All new cadets must return to post no later than 10 00 p m  More information about New Market Battlefield State Park VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   New Cadet Oath Ceremony  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Give Close Menu General Information Events Directions What you need to bring Matriculation Details Especially for parents  New Cadet Oath Ceremony Frequently Asked Questions Matriculation Day Brochure Katrina Butner Office Manager P   540  464 7104 F   540  464 7660 Email the Office 201 Smith Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  2445 New Cadet Oath Ceremony New Cadet Oath Ceremony Sunday  6 September New Market Battlefield State Historical Park  New Market  VA  Park opens at 9 am  Ceremony begins at 11 a m  Parade through New Market begins at 2 p m  New Cadets will take a historic tour and recite the Cadet Oath  They will charge across the battlefield exactly as the New Market cadets did on May 15  1864  Following the formal events  cadets will be able to enjoy a picnic lunch with their families and friends  Box lunches will be provided to all cadets  as well as for those family members who purchased tickets on Matriculation Day from the Parents Council Those who did not buy tickets on Matriculation Day for box lunches may purchase food in New Market or bring their own picnic lunch  The events at New Market conclude with a parade through the town after lunch  Cadets must return to Post on the buses  but will be able to sign out to spend time that evening with their parents in Lexington All new cadets must return to post no later than 10 00 p m  More information about New Market Battlefield State Park VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   New Cadet Oath Ceremony       Virginia Military Institute   New Cadet Oath Ceremony                    skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Give Close Menu General In